The paper discusses a communication library based on MPI and proposes a distributed sorting algorithm. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on the concept of communicators in MPI, which is related to parallel computing and distributed systems, indicating that the paper could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The proposed sorting algorithm is a variation of Quicksort, which is a well-known algorithm in the Performance (cs.PF) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of nonblocking collective operations, which is related to Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
